    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="601"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">War Trade Board Files: Japanese Tonnage
                    Negotiations, Vol. II</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the British Ministry of Shipping</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_FT1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fisher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chairman of the War Trade Board</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_MVC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCormick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">S 173</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVC1"
                            >McCormick</persName>
                    </hi>: In accordance with your suggestion,. I have already consulted Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_GEF1">Gay</persName> in this matter<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d601fn1">The chartering of Japanese vessels.</note> and I am happy
                    to say that as a result of urgent representations, the Ministry of Shipping in
                    London have agreed to take no action pending further consultation in order that
                    we may jointly decide what is best to be-done in the common interest.</p>
                <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas Fisher</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
